{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fc9ef569-76d3-4157-bb2a-c97abb8edc33","content":"\n\nHere are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (dotnet)**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity-based (JWT bearer)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n**Node.js** — Use Express/Fastify with libraries like `passport`, `jsonwebtoken`, or `express-oauth2-jwt-bearer`.\n\n**Python** — Use FastAPI or Django REST Framework with `python-jose`, `PyJWT`, or `django-oauth-toolkit`.\n\n**Authentication approaches:**\n| Approach | Best For |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth 2.0 / OIDC** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **API Keys** | Simple server-to-server |\n| **Cookie-based** | Traditional web apps |\n| **mTLS** | High-security service mesh |\n\nWhich stack are you targeting? I can scaffold a project for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"88d1f80e-5bd8-4943-a3be-54c83e16464e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":353},"id":"f124fd48-da2a-4cd5-b53c-af07ac30fd4e","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:50:15.496Z","parentId":"2be6499a-c319-4618-bcb0-65c47a007e03"}
